Alembic — async SQLAlchemy 2.0 migrations for LIMS.

Run from `backend/`:

    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
    alembic upgrade head
    alembic downgrade -1
    alembic history

Migration filename convention (per docs/integration_contract.md):

    <ordinal>_<member-letter>_<short_description>.py

Member letters reserved: a=Order/Approval, b=Sample/WIP, c=Machine/Recipe/Schedule,
d=ExperimentRun/Report, e=User/Role/SystemSetting/Issue/Notification/Dashboard.

This keeps autogenerate-created revisions from colliding on filenames when
multiple members work on the same week.
